Status Notes

   Local sites may have additional notes.

   When a site goes down...
   Streamflow data are collected by backup systems when a district server
   fails. In an emergency like a flood, we can read the backup data and
   report river stage and streamflow to authorities. We did exactly that
   when Hurricane Fran knocked out our North Carolina office. This is a
   fairly labor-intensive process, however, so we can't do it on a regular
   basis. We are working to provide automatic redundancy but are not yet
   there. We thank you for your patience.

   ----------

   For an explanation of stream gaging, see U.S. Geological Survey
   Circular 1123: Stream-Gaging Program of the U.S. Geological Survey by
   Kenneth L. Wahl, Wilbert O. Thomas, Jr., and Robert M. Hirsch.

   Streamflow Information for the Next Century - A Plan for the National
   Streamflow Information Program of the U.S. Geological Survey

